{
  "stem": "19923.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "My recollections at that period of time of a child were that I had a normal family life in the house.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Outside the house, it was not normal.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We knew from the earliest age that there was discrimination against the Jews in Germany.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And we knew from an early age how to walk in the streets to avoid trouble and what to do in order to not get ourselves hurt.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So at my earliest age, I already knew that I was different than most Germans-- or considered different than most Germans.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Let's talk a little about your life in the home.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You said that that was normal and you mentioned that you were a religious family.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Can you tell us about that?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I'm not sure about religious.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father was kosher.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He belonged to a little synagogue called the [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was Polish national, never became a German.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the friends and acquaintances were mostly Polish people that he knew.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he belonged to a synagogue, a little synagogue.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And of course, on Saturday he could not take the street car.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He'd have to walk.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And sometimes it would be a great distance to walk to the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So he-- my father was not that observant.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He would once in a while catch the streetcar to go to [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And of course, he was ostracized when he was discovered as having taken the streetcar on Shabbat or Yom Kippur or Rosh Hashanah.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But my recollection of-- of-- of those years is that my father was observant, but not necessarily religious.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That was the way of the Jewish people in Cologne.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "What else can I add?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "How were the holidays, the yomtevs, observed in your home?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We had Shabbat candles, we had challah, and we had the wine.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
